-- Florida Seeks Lender Meetings to `Redeem the Integrity' of Foreclosures
-- B y   D a v i d   M c L a u g h l i n
-- 2010-10-12T18:34:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/florida-seeks-lender-meetings-to-redeem-the-integrity-of-foreclosures.html
Florida Attorney General Bill
McCollum said he has requested a meeting with representatives of
mortgage lenders including Bank of America Corp., JPMorgan Chase
& Co. and Goldman Sachs Group Inc. unit Litton Loan Servicing to
“discuss ways to promptly and effectively redeem the integrity
of the foreclosure process,” according to an e-mailed statement
today from his office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David McLaughlin in New York at 
